By December, the region recorded 289,210 cases and 5,514 deaths.In Somalia, the epicentre of terrorism and insecurity in the Horn of Africa, security incidents stood at 235 by the end of January 2020.Tensions also escalated between Ethiopia, Sudan and Egypt over the Grand Ethiopian Renaissance Dam  on the Blue Nile River. An air of optimism greeted the year 2020, but it has turned out to be the Horn of Africa’s — and indeed the World’s —  worst Year— an annus horribilis. Many are happy that this “horrible year” has come to an end.
The year opened with the tragic outbreak of the 2019–2020 desert locust invasion, the worst in 70 years in Kenya and the deadliest in 25 years in Ethiopia and Somalia, which has left in its trail a debilitating food insecurity compounded by the outbreak of corona virus (Covid-19) pandemic.



